'''Tullberg's woodpecker''' ('''''Campethera tullbergi''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Picidae]].
It is found in western [[Cameroon]], adjacent [[Nigeria]], and [[Bioko]] island.

The common name and Latin binomial commemorates the Swedish zoologist [[Tycho Fredrik Hugo Tullberg]] (1842-1920).<ref>{{cite book|last=Beolens|first=Bo|title=Whose Bird? Men and Women Commemorated in the Common Names of Birds|year=2003|publisher=Christopher Helm|location=London|page=344|author2=Watkins, Michael  }}</ref>

